////////////////////////////////
// ========================== //
// Journal entries for quests //
// ========================== //
////////////////////////////////
@20003 = ~Someone wants to meet you at the Smoldering Corpse Bar~
@20004 = ~I received a mysterious message upon my return to Sigil. It turns out that someone called Tergush'tekhn at the back of the Smoldering Corpse Bar has some information and possibly a well-paid task for me. I should go and check it out.~
@20005 = ~I received a message upon my return to Sigil from a mysterious messenger. He wanted to deliver it to me, but I told him I am not interested in what he had to say. If I change my mind, I can find him by the black obelisk.~
@20006 = ~The stranger from the Smoldering Corpse Bar turned out to be a fiend, a red abishai named Tergush'tekhn. He claimed to know me and made me a very interesting offer.~
@20007 = ~Rescue your old friend who is lost in Cania, the 8th layer of the Hells~
@20008 = ~I agreed to search for an erinyes lost deep in Baator. Apparently, she is an old friend of mine who can shed some light on my origins, which may allow me to find another path. I must go to the Civic Festhall and find Professor Mawu, then ask her about the hopping portal to Cania, which is located somewhere in Sigil.~
@20009 = ~Meeting with Mawu revealed that hopping portals appear cyclically, often in the same place, and usually do not require sophisticated keys. I also learned that Manohae liked to eat various things. To find out what he had consumed before disappearing, I should find his friend, a kocrachon named Elvra Syne. In the meantime, I should head back to the fiends.~
@20010 = ~The devils finally told me to go to the Ditch. To get there, I should employ the services of a "small mortal" just outside the Smoldering Corpse Bar. Somewhere in the Ditch, an imp named Prod should be waiting for me. He has been doing reconnaissance for a few cycles, trying to locate the portal. ~
@20011 = ~I think I found Prod. A gang of local thugs is holding him hostage at a tavern called the Rivergate. I need to find a way to set him free and talk to him.~
@20012 = ~Prod regained his freedom from Black Joseph and his goons. I should talk to him and see what he had learned about the portal to Cania.~
@20013 = ~Prod found a clue to locating the portal. It involves talking to a renegade, frostbitten wererat that the yugoloths are looking for. We need to contact one of those yugoloths, Wotyrxil from the Styx Oarsman. Prod also blurted out that the erinyes we are looking for is a concubine of Levistus, one of the Lords of the Nine Hells. This is quite important information that the devils failed to mention. However, for now I should focus on meeting Wotyrxil. ~
@20014 = ~A marraenoloth named Wotyrxil informed me that he had been attacked and robbed by the wererats. He wants me to find them and retrieve his stolen flute. One of the wererats should know something about the portal to Cania. I have yet to decide whether I want to work with the fiend. I can find him on the upper floor of the Styx Oarsman.~
@20015 = ~I agreed to help Wotyrxil retrieve his flute from the wererat thieves. He gave me a password that opens a new door for me, to an inn called the Rat and Splat. It might be a good starting point in my search for the thieves. Among them, I should find the renegade wererat with a frostbitten tail. ~
@20016 = ~Orville, the owner of the Rat and Splat, revealed to me that he knows exactly where Fragile-Tail, the frostbitten wererat, is. Supposedly, he is the only survivor of the band of wererats who attacked Wotyrxil and, fortunately, the only one I need to find the portal. I should ask Orville how to meet the poor sod. ~
@20017 = ~Orville will introduce me to Fragile-Tail, the frostbitten wererat who may have information about the portal to Cania if I help him with his local competition. I am to eliminate the priest Dopilp and his gang of troublesome kuo-toa from the nearby flooded area.~
@20018 = ~I agreed to kill the kuo-toa and their spiritual leader for Orville from the Rat and Splat. In return, he will lead me to Fragile-Tail, the frostbitten wererat who may have information about the portal to Cania. All I need to do is spill some fish blood in the flooded area.~
@20019 = ~I found the kuo-toa I was asked to kill for Orville from the Rat and Splat. In return, he will lead me to Fragile-Tail, the frostbitten wererat who may have information about the portal to Cania. The kuo-toa lurk in a massive cavern beneath the flooded area.~
@20020 = ~Dopilp is gone and will not trouble the wererats any longer. I have to go back to the Rat and Splat for my reward from Orville, who promised to lead me to Fragile-Tail, the frostbitten wererat who may have information about the portal to Cania.~
@20021 = ~Since the kuo-toa are no longer an issue, Orville will let me into the back room to meet Fragile-Tail, the frostbitten wererat who may have information about the portal to Cania. I have the key to the door at the top of the stairs at the back of the inn.~
@20022 = ~Orville will let me into the back room to meet Fragile-Tail, the frostbitten wererat who may have information about the portal to Cania. I have the key to the door at the top of the stairs at the back of the inn.~
@20023 = ~Fragile-Tail's life is a series of misfortunes, but he revealed to me where and when the hopping portal I am looking for appears: at midnight in the ruined clock tower at the center of the flooded area. Interestingly, it only allows four creatures to pass through. I should report back to the fiends at the Smoldering Corpse Bar. I still need protection from the cold and the key, of course.~
@20024 = ~The Rat and Splat has been deratized. It seems I will have to get my answers about the location of the hopping portal to Cania from Fragile-Tail's dead body.~
@20025 = ~Fragile-Tail's diary revealed where and when the hopping portal I was looking for appears: at midnight in the ruined clock tower at the center of the flooded area. Interestingly, it only allows four creatures to pass through. I should report back to the fiends at the Smoldering Corpse Bar. I still need protection from the cold and the key, of course.~
@20026 = ~I already have the location of the portal, the key to the portal, a planned route back, and protection against the deadly frost of the Hells. It is time to go to the clock tower at antipeak and travel to Cania to find and rescue Fury-Vehement.~
@20027 = ~I passed through the portal to Cania. The robe I got from the fiends is doing its job: I am still alive. In the distance, I can see the lights of Mephistar, where Fury was last seen. It looks like I have a long walk ahead of me, but first I have a meeting with my guide in this place, Gemariel. He should be around here somewhere.~
@20028 = ~An ambush awaited me in Cania. Akershus the Bard and his entourage of devils were waiting for Prod. It turns out that Prod, as well as the other devils, once served Mammon. The situation is getting complicated. Prod knew the way back, and without him, I do not know what to do. All I can do now is find my local guide, Gemariel, and continue looking for Fury. He should be somewhere around here.~
@20029 = ~Rezerwacja~
