@20062 = ~Help a blacksmith from the Ditch with his thug problem~
@20063 = ~I asked the local blacksmith, Adam, if he had any work for me. It turns out he has a problem with a local thug. If I want, I can return to him and hear more about it. I will find him right under the broken chronometer near the Styx Oarsman.~
@20064 = ~I agreed to help Adam and teach the thug a lesson. I should find him by the statue of the goddess Athena.~
@20065 = ~blank~
@20066 = ~The suspicious tiefling has left Sigil and will no longer pester Adam. He probably returned to Tradegate. Maybe we should send some kind of warning there. I should report back to the blacksmith.~
@20067 = ~I informed Adam, the blacksmith, that his problems with the thug are over.~
@20068 = ~Find the stolen item belonging to the innkeeper of the Rivergate~
@20069 = ~Brill, the innkeeper of the Rivergate Tavern, will help me with the portal trap if I recover something that a gith named Ikss'odes, his former employee, stole from him. I have to consider whether I want to work for a slaad, though. If needed, I can always find him at the Rivergate.~
@20070 = ~I agreed to help Brill, the innkeeper of the Rivergate Tavern, find his former employee, Ikss'odes, and recover what he stole. Apparently, he lives somewhere near the Zaddfum Trestle. In return, Brill will tell me how to bypass the portal trap and reach Prod.~
@20071 = ~To find Ikss'odes, I was directed to Mare, the thief's beloved. I should find her near the Vertical Sea, where she offers... certain services. Meeting her is the next step to bypass the portal trap at the Rivergate Tavern.~
@20072 = ~I found Mare, Ikss'odes's partner. I just need to learn from her where he is so I can retrieve Brill's stolen item and get past the portal trap at his tavern.~
@20073 = ~Mare revealed to me that Ikss'odes is simply hiding in his own home in the center of the settlement. She gave me her key. I should look for the door near the medical tent so I can retrieve Brill's stolen item and get past the portal trap at his tavern.~
@20074 = ~blank~
@20075 = ~Find some books for the modron librarian~
@20076 = ~The modron librarian commissioned me to find at least seven books and deliver them to him as part of the fight against illiteracy in the Hive. He offers a reward after seven copies have been delivered to him.

Below is a list of books sought by the modron librarian:

- The Plane Truth
- Fire and Dust
- The Seafarer's Arch or Final Port-of-Call
- The Ditch - Of Sigil and the Sea
- The Day of Grace
- The Analects of Sigil
- The Seven Wonders of the Multiverse
- The Mortuary Receiving Room Logbook
- Tome of Bone and Ash
- Codex of the Inconceivable
- The Grimoire of Pestilential Thought (warning: dangerous)

The list is open, and I am sure the librarian would be happy to accept items not on the list. He may have trouble showing enthusiasm, though.~
@20077 = ~I delivered the books. In return, I received an interesting tome: The Planewalker's Grimoire.~
@20079 = ~The thief Ikss'odes is dead. He was not much of a threat. I have to find the item he stole and return it to Brill at the Rivergate Tavern so that he can help me bypass the portal trap and get to Prod.~
@20080 = ~I recovered the vial of karach for Brill. I have to return it to the Rivergate Tavern so that he can help me bypass the portal trap and get to Prod.~
@20081 = ~The karach will not be returning to Brill. He will probably not be happy with this turn of events. I may have to find another way to bypass the portal trap or rely on the slaad's goodwill back at the Rivergate Tavern.~
@20082 = ~After listening to the githzerai, I decided that the crime should be pinned on someone else, for example Joseph. Maybe I can kill two birds with one stone. I should head back to the Rivergate Tavern and talk to Brill.~
@20083 = ~After listening to the githzerai, I decided that I do not want to get involved in this conflict. Let us hope that the slaad will have another task for me. I should head back to the Rivergate Tavern and talk to Brill.~
@20084 = ~Brill once again has possession of his karach. In gratitude, he gave me a chalice that is meant to serve as an anti-key to the portal. I can now get to Joseph and Prod.~
@20085 = ~Brill will no longer be running the Rivergate Tavern. Maybe I will find something among his belongings that will allow me to bypass the portal trap and get to Joseph and Prod.~
@20086 = ~Discover the key to the hopping portal to Cania~
@20087 = ~Mawu knew the Sensate mentioned by the fiends who found his way to Cania. It turns out that he liked to bite off parts of various creatures' bodies. It is possible that he did not have the key in his pocket, but in his stomach. I need to find a kocrachon named Elvra Syne. He often dined with Manohae and may know what he had eaten before disappearing. In the meantime, I should head back to the fiends.~
@20088 = ~Haer'Dalis, an actor from the Beneathmask Drama Hall, told me that Elvra Syne frequents the Styx Oarsman, a tavern here in the Ditch. That should allow me to find him more quickly and learn what Manohae had consumed that served as the key to the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20089 = ~Elvra Syne informed me that Manohae had bitten off a piece of a frost giant's hand just before he disappeared. It is highly likely that it was a bone from this frost giant that opened the portal. In order to locate the frost giants currently residing in Sigil, it is best to find someone from the Hall of Records. I can find a division of the Hall in Ysgard, apparently connected to the Ditch by a portal nearby. But where is it located? I should probably ask the Fated, or better yet, their enemies, the Doomguard.~
@20090 = ~It turns out that Haer'Dalis from the Beneathmask Drama Hall knows how to get to Ysgard from the Ditch. I will gain access to the portal if I get involved in a conflict between the Fated and the Doomguard, two of Sigil's warring factions. In Ysgard, I will surely find representatives of the Hall of Records, who will help me locate a frost giant, or perhaps I will even encounter a member of that race there. I need their bones to get to Cania. If I decide to follow this lead, Haer'Dalis is waiting in the theater.~
@20091 = ~I witnessed a quarrel on the stairs. Someone mentioned a "wretched excuse of an actor."~
@20092 = ~I witnessed a quarrel on the stairs leading to the main part of the settlement. One member of the Fated and two Doomguards were arguing about an actor named Haer'Dalis. It sounded rather serious.~
@20093 = ~I met Haer'Dalis. He is a Sinker and the actor the Fated are searching for. He asked me to find Ulfbrand, a high-ranking factotum of the Fated who is responsible for the manhunt. I must either eliminate him or, preferably, convince him to leave Haer'Dalis alone. I have not yet decided whether I want to involve myself in a heated conflict between factions, but if I choose to do so, I should find Haer'Dalis at the Beneathmask Drama Hall.~
@20094 = ~I agreed to help Haer'Dalis, the persecuted Doomguard actor. He asked me to find Ulfbrand, a high-ranking factotum of the Fated who is responsible for the manhunt. I must either eliminate him or, preferably, convince him to leave Haer'Dalis alone. Ulfbrand resides in the Hall of Records in Ysgard. I should be able to find a portal leading there somewhere near the beach. Haer'Dalis does not know its precise location, but he gave me the key to it. While in Ysgard, I should remember my main objective: speaking with someone in the Hall of Records who can lead me closer to obtaining the key to Cania.~
@20095 = ~I arrived in Ysgard. The portal transported me to a lone earthberg that is quite small. It should not be too difficult to locate Ulfbrand and speak with him. In the meantime, I should not forget my main objective: speaking with someone in the Hall of Records who can lead me closer to obtaining the key to Cania.~
@20096 = ~Investigate a conflict between factions~
@20097 = ~In Ysgard, I met Tasslewick Drohm, a representative of the Hall of Records. It turns out that there are currently no frost giants in Sigil, but Ulfbrand, whom I was supposed to speak to on behalf of the Doomguard, possesses an earring made from the bone of such a giant. Unfortunately, he has only one, but it should suffice as a key. I must obtain it somehow. Ulfbrand resides inside the sole structure on this earthberg. It seems I must meet with him for two reasons...~
@20098 = ~I met with Ulfbrand, a factotum of the Fated, and tried to convince him to stop persecuting the Doomguard actor Haer'Dalis. He refused. I suppose it is time for plan B.~
@20099 = ~I met with Ulfbrand and managed to convince him to resign from his post completely and call off the search for Haer'Dalis. I discovered that the Fated's position in the region was weak, and he would most likely prefer to return to his old warrior life. That was enough to make him step down. He gave me his earring after I promised that I would find the other one and return both to him. The key to the hopping portal to Cania is now in my possession. I should also head back to the theater and share the good news before the Fated resume their search under new leadership.~
@20100 = ~I stole Ulfbrand's earring right under his nose. I no longer need to involve myself in this conflict unless I really want to. The key to the hopping portal to Cania is now in my possession.~
@20101 = ~I angered Ulfbrand. I was not able to kill him in Ysgard, so I must return to Sigil and side with the Doomguard if I want to resolve the upcoming conflict. Hopefully, it will end with Ulfbrand's demise so I can obtain his earring. I need it to open the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20102 = ~Staying loyal to the Doomguard, I lied to Ulfbrand and told him I do not know where Haer'Dalis is. I promised to discover his location and help organize a raid. I should return to the Doomguard and inform them about everything. We can use that knowledge to our advantage. I still need to find a way to obtain Ulfbrand's earring, which will serve as the key to the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20103 = ~Staying loyal to the Doomguard, I lied to Ulfbrand. I told him I would slay Haer'Dalis myself, so there would be no need to organize a raid. I should return to the Doomguard and inform them about everything. I still need to find a way to obtain Ulfbrand's earring, which will serve as the key to the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20104 = ~I returned to the theater and reported what had happened. Knowing that battle is unavoidable, we decided to lure Ulfbrand to a more easily defensible location. I should go and deliver the false information to him. Hopefully, the ambush will end in his demise so I can obtain his earring. I need it to open the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20105 = ~Ulfbrand is now gathering troops to lead the raid to the wrong location. I should use the letters I have been given to call upon my allies and travel to the raid site. Hopefully, the ambush will end with Ulfbrand's demise so I can obtain his earring. I need it to open the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20106 = ~The plan was a success. The Doomguard are victorious, at least for now, and the troupe is free to leave the city and move to the Prime Material Plane. I received my reward as well, the bone earring that opens the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20107 = ~The plan was a failure. We suffered a crushing defeat at the hands of the Fated. The troupe is dead. Fortunately, I have already stolen the bone earring that opens the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20108 = ~The plan was a failure. We suffered a crushing defeat at the hands of the Fated. The troupe is dead. Regardless, I still need the earring. Perhaps Ulfbrand is willing to talk about it now that his hunt is over.~
@20109 = ~Ulfbrand is not sure which side I was on, but he is so pleased with his victory that he has agreed to lend me his earring, provided I find the other one and return both to him. Should I fail to do that, the wrath of the entire Debt Collection Division will be upon me. The key to the hopping portal to Cania is now in my possession.~
@20110 = ~The conflict got out of hand. The Lady of Pain arrived at the scene and slew everyone. I survived only because I was lucky enough to retreat before her intervention. This faction skirmish is definitely over. I suspect I will find the earring somewhere among the ashes. I am nearly in possession of the key that opens the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20111 = ~I decided to side with the Fated. I promised to go and kill Haer'Dalis myself. It should not be too difficult. The Doomguard trust me enough to let me near him. In return, I may receive the bone earring that opens the hopping portal to Cania, as long as I find the other one and return both to them.~
@20112 = ~I decided to side with the Fated. We are to organize a raid on the theater. I should use the letters I have been given to call upon my allies and travel to the raid site. In return, I may receive the bone earring that opens the hopping portal to Cania, as long as I find the other one and return both.~
@20113 = ~The raid was a success. Haer'Dalis and his troupe are no more. Ulfbrand agreed to give me his earring as long as I find the other one and return both to him. Should I fail to do that, the wrath of the entire Debt Collection Division will be upon me. The key to the hopping portal to Cania is now in my possession.~
@20114 = ~The raid was a success. Haer'Dalis and his troupe are no more. Ulfbrand wanted to give me the earring as a reward, but he discovered it was missing. He blamed the City of Doors and left, a thousand vile curses falling from his lips. The key to the hopping portal to Cania is already in my possession.~
@20115 = ~The raid was a failure. The Doomguard are victorious, at least for now, and the troupe is free to leave the city and move to the Prime Material Plane. I was allowed to leave despite my treachery. I should look for Ulfbrand's bone earring among the ashes. I need it to open the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20116 = ~The raid was a failure. The Doomguard are victorious, at least for now, and the troupe is free to leave the city and move to the Prime Material Plane. I was allowed to walk away despite my treachery. Fortunately, I have already stolen the earring. The key to the hopping portal to Cania is in my possession.~
@20117 = ~I slew Haer'Dalis. I should report back to Ulfbrand and bring him the good news. In exchange, I hope to receive his earring, as long as I promise to find the other one and return both.~
@20118 = ~Ulfbrand was pleased to hear about the death of the troupe. He agreed to give me his earring as long as I find the other one and return both to him. Should I fail to do that, the wrath of the entire Debt Collection Division will be upon me. The key to the hopping portal to Cania is now in my possession.~
@20119 = ~Ulfbrand was pleased to hear about the death of the troupe. The conflict is over. The key to the hopping portal to Cania is already in my possession.~
@20120 = ~Help a fiend find his friend~
@20121 = ~Agraval, the baernaloth from the Styx Oarsman, has lost his companion, a modron. The situation seems quite strange. I do not know whether I want to get involved. If I change my mind, I can find Agraval on the second flood of the Oarsman.~
@20122 = ~I have already seen the modron that Agraval is looking for. I told the fiend about it, and he hurried to find him. Maybe I will meet them at Suicide Falls, where I last saw Patch.~
@20123 = ~I lied to Agraval and sent him to one of the modrons I saw in the area. I hope I do not meet him again. He certainly will not be happy with this turn of events.~
@20124 = ~Everyone turned against me. When Ulfbrand falls, I should look for his earring among the ashes. I need to get it to open the hopping portal to Cania.~
@20125 = ~I agreed to help find the missing modron. Agraval must care about him very much, because he pulled out his own tooth and gave it to me as bait to send Patch on the right track.~
@20126 = ~I found Patch, but instead of directing him to his "owner," I restored his original personality. He immediately returned to Mechanus. Agraval is unlikely to be pleased.~
@20127 = ~Following the scent of his owner, Patch the modron headed toward the inn. I wonder if he will make it.~
@20128 = ~I told Agraval directly that I had reprogrammed his friend and given him his freedom back. As expected, he did not take it well...~
@20129 = ~The fiend and his friend are together again, and both seem overjoyed. I am not sure whether this is truly a happy ending, but it looks like it is.~
@20130 = ~blank~
@20131 = ~I lied to Agraval and sent him to one of the modrons I saw in the area. I hope I do not meet him again. He certainly will not be happy with this turn of events.~
@20132 = ~I told the fiend where his dog was, and he hurried to find him. Maybe I will meet them at Suicide Falls, where I last saw Patch.~
@20133 = ~Agraval and his two henchmen surprised me in the center of the settlement, accusing me of lying. Well, they were right. Blood was shed.~
@20134 = ~A furious Agraval and his two henchmen ambushed me in the center of the settlement, accusing me of reprogramming the modron. Well, they were right. Blood was shed.~
@20135 = ~Learn more about a mysterious ancient relief in Sigil~
@20136 = ~Vinrogé, an archaeologist, found a relief that contradicts the rules imposed by the Lady of Pain. Unfortunately, he cannot examine it because it is densely overgrown with razorvine. If I decide to help him, I can find him in the flooded area.~
@20137 = ~I agreed to help the archaeologist remove the stubborn growth so that he could continue his research. The stone covered with razorvine is located right next to him in the flooded area.~
@20138 = ~The razorvine did not give up without a fight. It turns out that quite large creatures were hiding within it. It is time to hear what Vinrogé has to say about the uncovered relief.~
@20139 = ~With the razorvine no longer in his way, Vinrogé was able to examine the relief. It turned out to be an image of Ishtar, an Anunnaki goddess of war and love who once reigned in a city in Elysium. It is unclear how she placed the relief here, right under the nose of the Lady of Pain.~
@20140 = ~Vinrogé mentioned a museum in Mephistar that holds a great deal of information about the ancient Anunnaki deities. I am going to visit Mephistar soon, so I could try to help him.~
@20141 = ~I confessed to Vinrogé that I was heading to Mephistar, so I could try to help him. He needs me to find clay tablets stolen from the kingdom of the goddess Inanna. I will have to keep that in mind once I reach that hellish city.~
@20142 = ~It seems that I will not visit Mephistar after all. I will not be able to find the clay tablets in the local museum.~
@20143 = ~It seems that I have arrived in the abandoned divine realm of the goddess Inanna, from which the tablets were originally stolen before being placed in Mephistar. Perhaps I will find something here that will be useful to Vinrogé.~
