@20166 = ~Aid an angel in the slums~
@20167 = ~Alviro, a celestial who cares for the needy on a cliff near the Ditch, wants to recover a sword that is important to him. If I decide to help, I can find him near his medical tent.~
@20168 = ~I agreed to help Alviro recover a holy blade forged by Girru, an Anunnaki. The weapon is currently in the possession of Kabatum, a dangerous concordant killer. The angel warned me to avoid direct conflict with him. Kabatum lives in a white marble residence hidden beyond the Vertical Sea.~
@20169 = ~It turned out that the sword I took from Kabatum was the very weapon sought by the angel on the cliff.~
@20170 = ~I provoked a fight with Kabatum. I will have to take his sword by force. Once I recover it, I must meet the deva Alviro at his medical tent on the cliff.~
@20171 = ~I managed to recover the sword from Kabatum. All he wanted from me was an explanation of my motives. Now it is time to meet Alviro at his medical tent on the cliff.~
@20172 = ~Alviro recovered the Anunnaki sword. He rewarded me before leaving Sigil to return to Mount Celestia, much to the dismay of the poor residents of the Ditch.~
@20173 = ~I returned the Anunnaki sword to Alviro, but the angel saw something in me and decided that I should keep it. I swore to use it only for good. I hope I do not tarnish such a remarkable gift.~
@20174 = ~Alviro refused to let me keep the Anunnaki sword. A fight broke out between us, causing panic among his patients.~
@20175 = ~A fight broke out between Alviro and me. I mistreated his patients, and he decided to show me the error of my ways.~
@20176 = ~Deal with the queue at the doctor's 
~
@20177 = ~A celestial is healing people on a cliff near the Ditch. Unfortunately, he does not have time to speak with me. Maybe if I help him with some of the patients, he might spare me a moment.~
@20178 = ~I helped one patient, or at least they have left the queue. I probably need to help more of them if I want the deva to find time to talk to me.~
@20179 = ~I managed to help two patients leave the queue. I probably need to help more of them if I want the deva to find time to talk to me.~
@20180 = ~Only two patients remain in the queue. Maybe I should try speaking to the deva now. If he is still reluctant to spare me some time, I can try helping another patient.~
@20181 = ~Only a single patient remains. Surely the deva will have time for me now.~
@20182 = ~I managed to take care of all the patients. It is time to speak with the celestial by the medical tent.~
@20183 = ~Thanks to my help with the patients, the deva was finally able to take a break and speak with me.~
@20184 = ~A fight broke out between Alviro and me. I mistreated his patients, and he decided to show me the error of my ways.~
@20185 = ~Uncover the horror of the Ditch~
@20186 = ~I learned that people have been disappearing in the area lately, leaving behind only the smell of fish. Recently, that scent has spread across the beach. Maybe I should go there and take a look when I have some free time.~
@20187 = ~At the pitiful excuse for a beach in the Ditch, I met a strange beachgoer. One of the fish people, a kuo-toa, is lurking suspiciously nearby and giving off a fishy smell. I should probably do something about him.~
@20188 = ~The creepy kuo-toa will no longer disturb the ladies. Unfortunately, he did not provide much information except for a piece of slobbery string.~
@20189 = ~A local string merchant at the market recognized the string the kuo-toa had lost at the beach. About two weeks ago, a priestess of a deity from the Elemental Plane of Water bought the same type of waterproof string from him. Apparently, she spoke at length with Adam, the blacksmith.~
@20190 = ~Adam the blacksmith admitted that the priestess bought rust-proof tools from him, as if she planned to spend a long time in a damp place. A flooded part of the city is nearby, destroyed by the growth of razorvine. Perhaps I should search the flooded buildings.~
@20191 = ~I found a kuo-toa lair. They nest in a cave beneath a flooded building in an area ravaged by razorvine. It is time to confront them.~
@20192 = ~I found a kuo-toa lair. They nest in a cave beneath a flooded building in an area ravaged by razorvine. It is time to confront them.~
@20193 = ~The kuo-toa have begun to worship me. I am not sure how this will comply with Sigil's rules.~
@20194 = ~The kuo-toa will no longer kidnap people. I ordered them to behave peacefully.~
@20195 = ~The kuo-toa will no longer kidnap people. I have ordered them to behave peacefully. In fact, they will go to the surface and help people openly. The horror of the Ditch has come to an end.~
@20196 = ~The kuo-toa have begun to worship Bhaal, the god of murder, led by their former prisoner, Kilthas Dar'Abomyn. The horror of the Ditch has only just begun.~
@20197 = ~The kuo-toa have begun to worship Kiaransalee, my goddess of undeath. Priest Dopilp will continue his work, but instead of wasting corpses, they will be animated as zombies to spread the good news. The horror of the Ditch has only just begun.~
@20198 = ~The kuo-toa have begun to worship Kiaransalee, my goddess of undeath. The priest Dopilp did not fall in line, so he was dealt with swiftly. The horror of the Ditch has only just begun.~
@20199 = ~The kuo-toa have left the city in search of "deeper waters." The horror of the Ditch has come to an end.~
@20200 = ~The kuo-toa are no longer a threat. The horror of the Ditch has come to an end.~
@20201 = ~The kuo-toa and their new spiritual leader, Kilthas, were destroyed. The horror of the Ditch has come to an end.~
@20202 = ~Discover the wererat temple and its treasures~
@20203 = ~To save its life, the book mimic showed me a temple with a large statue of a wererat. I also noticed a treasure chest there, which caught my attention. I already have the key, the sketch beneath the entry, and I think it should be enough to open it. But where is this temple? Perhaps the local wererats can tell me something.~
@20204 = ~Orville, the Rat and Splat barkeep, confirmed the existence of the temple of Squerrik in Sigil, but he does not know where it is. An aggressive sect of worshippers has taken up residence there. Apparently, the best source of information about the place is children's gossip. Are there even any children roaming around?~
@20205 = ~The children who like to dress up as devils revealed a secret to me. Apparently, there is a hidden portal among the pipes that leads to the temple. The key to opening it is a necklace made of fifteen rat tails. I need to collect the tails and find someone who can weave them into a necklace.~
@20206 = ~Beatha, the jeweler from the upper floor of the Styx Oarsman, will be able to weave a necklace from rat tails to serve as the key to the portal leading to Squerrik's temple. I just need to obtain fifteen rat tails from somewhere.~
@20207 = ~Beatha, the demonic jeweler from the Styx Oarsman, made me a necklace out of rat tails. It should open the portal among the pipes that leads to a hidden temple.~
@20208 = ~I found the way to the temple. It appears to be located beneath the surface of Sigil. It is full of aggressive wererats. The treasure chest must be close.~
@20209 = ~As soon as my gaze fell on the chest, it opened in a flash of magical energy. It appears this was due to the key I remembered from the pages of the book mimic. The secret treasure is now mine.~
@20210 = ~Befriend the pale woman on the edge~
@20211 = ~I met an unusual woman near the market, very pale and dressed all in black. She is standing right on the edge of the cliff. There is something extremely odd about her. I feel like I should try to befriend her.~
@20212 = ~The pale woman fell off the cliff into the waters below. She appeared to be smiling on her way down, so either she was happy about it or... I may see her again yet.~
@20213 = ~The pale woman and I have found common ground. She considers me a friend, but she still refuses to reveal anything about herself. I need to earn her trust, but I do not know how.~
@20214 = ~The pale woman showed interest in the old amulet I found in Ysgard. It turns out that she follows an old deity of decay, Moander. The amulet bears his symbol.~
@20215 = ~I handed over the amulet I found in Ysgard to the pale woman. It was useless to me anyway, while she seems to treasure it. She definitely trusts me more now. It is finally time to get to know her better.~
@20216 = ~I did not intend to give the amulet to the woman, but she took it anyway and dove into the water with it. I have a feeling I will meet her again one day.~
@20217 = ~I finally had an honest discussion with the pale woman, whose name I learned is Belle, about her beliefs and her deity, Moander. However, she did not survive it.~
@20218 = ~I finally had an honest discussion with the pale woman, whose name I have learned is Belle, about her beliefs and her deity, Moander. Our bond grew deeper, but she had to bid me farewell as she needs to prepare for a pilgrimage to Offalmound, Moander's old divine realm. Maybe we will meet again one day.~
@20219 = ~Rezerwacja~
@20220 = ~Rezerwacja~
@20221 = ~Rezerwacja~
@20222 = ~Rezerwacja~
@20223 = ~Rezerwacja~
@20224 = ~Rezerwacja~
@20225 = ~Rezerwacja~
@20226 = ~Rezerwacja~
@20227 = ~Get to the bottom of the plague of threes~
@20228 = ~A wererat named Poirat at the Rat and Splat Inn told me about his search. He is trying to track down one of the perpetrators behind the "heist of the decade," who is supposedly hiding somewhere near the Ditch.~
@20229 = ~A wererat named Poirat at the Rat and Splat Inn told me about his search. He is trying to track down one of the perpetrators behind the "heist of the decade," who is supposedly hiding somewhere near the Ditch. Finding them will be like searching for a needle in a haystack, but there are a few leads I can pursue, including a connection to the "plague of threes" and a strange skeleton wandering through the local taverns. I offered to help with the investigation.~
@20230 = ~The skeleton that frequents the local taverns remains unresponsive to my attempts to contact it. Perhaps the innkeepers know more about it.~
@20231 = ~A local barkeep told me to ask Zegonz Vlaric, the innkeeper at the Styx Oarsman, about the strange skeleton.~
@20232 = ~Zegonz revealed that a certain scientist, Krauss Schneider, once took an interest in the skeleton. Where can I find a scientist near the Ditch?~
@20233 = ~Krauss Schneider possesses a forbidden sensory stone that drives all who use it mad. Magical identification revealed that the memories locked within it belong to Tripler, the strange skeleton.~
@20234 = ~Krauss Schneider possesses a forbidden sensory stone that drives all who use it mad. Magical identification revealed that the memories locked within it belong to Tripler, the strange skeleton. I offered to use the forbidden sensory stone, and Krauss eagerly agreed to observe my reactions firsthand.~
@20235 = ~The memories stored within the sensory stone revealed a great deal. The skeleton was once a man named Paw, a notorious thief from the Ditch whom none other than I recruited. One of my past incarnations hired him to rob the bastion of the Fated in Ysgard. The key to communicating with him is to speak the way he thinks, which means repeating everything three times. I should find the skeleton in one of the inns and try to learn more from him.~
@20236 = ~Tripler told me that Zegonz Vlaric, the innkeeper at the Styx Oarsman, has the missing part of the key, a jade jaw. Tripler sold it to him while he was still alive.~
@20237 = ~Zegonz had the missing part of the key, a jade jaw. He was not aware that the skeleton was, in fact, Paw. Now Tripler can finally rest in peace. It is time to speak with Poirat at the Rat and Splat Inn.~
@20238 = ~I gave the jade jaw to Poirat. It turns out he knew more than I had thought. In any case, the job is done, the reward is mine, and Tripler can finally be at peace.~
@20239 = ~I met with Poirat. It turns out he knew more than I had thought. He had been using me. The conversation turned into a confrontation. On him, I found a second part of the key. But what does the now complete jade skull open? All I know is that it was stolen from the Fated in Ysgard.~
@20240 = ~I discovered the purpose of the jade skull. It opens a portal from the Fated Hall in Ysgard to a secret storage room in Alfheim. It appears to regulate access to a large magical alcohol depot.~
@20241 = ~On my return from Alfheim, I was approached by a local skald. He wanted the skull in exchange for keeping quiet about us stealing the contents of the warehouse. It was a fair deal, so I gave it to him. Fortunately, he was not interested in what we had already taken from Alfheim.~
@20242 = ~On my return from Ysgard, I was approached by a local skald. He wanted the skull in exchange for keeping quiet about us stealing the contents of the warehouse. I refused his terms, and a scuffle ensued. The skull remained in my possession.~
@20243 = ~Rescue the garb of a gullible goober from a gumptious gal~
@20244 = ~I met a naked young man hiding in a nook near the stairs. He revealed that a lady in a red dress took his clothes to clean them after providing her "services." It appears she robbed him.~
@20245 = ~I met a naked young man hiding in a nook near the stairs. He said a woman in a red dress took his clothes to clean them after providing her "services." It appears she robbed him. I promised to find her and confront her about it.~
@20246 = ~The woman in a red dress had no qualms about admitting to her crime. However, I could not get anything else out of her, so I left her alone. I should tell the young man that he will have to go home naked.~
@20247 = ~The woman in a red dress had no qualms about admitting to her crime. I could not get anything else out of her, and the situation turned violent. Unfortunately, I could not recover the clothes, as they had already been sold, but at least justice prevailed. I should tell the young man that he will have to go home naked.~
@20248 = ~The woman in a red dress had no qualms about admitting to her crime. She sold the clothes at the local market, so I should check the merchant stalls.~
@20249 = ~Among the merchants is a trader who sells clothes and fabrics. She appears to have the clothing that was taken from the young man who was robbed.~
@20250 = ~Among the merchants is a trader who sells clothes and fabrics. She also had the stolen garb that the woman in a red dress had brought her. I bought them back at a rather exorbitant price. I can now return them to the young man by the stairs.~
@20251 = ~The young man by the stairs got his stolen clothes back. With a lesson learned and a broken heart, he ran home fully clothed.~
@20252 = ~I told the young man by the stairs that his clothes were gone. With a lesson learned and a broken heart, he ran home naked.~
@20253 = ~I told the young man by the stairs that his clothes were gone. With a lesson learned and a broken heart, he ran home naked. I laughed at him as he left. Serves him right.~
@20254 = ~The young man by the stairs got his stolen clothes back. As payment for my services, I took the only thing he had left: his clothes. With two lessons learned, he ran home naked.~
@20255 = ~Assist the Office of Vermin and Disease Control~
@20256 = ~By Suicide Falls, I met Pabeshts, an official of the Office of Vermin and Disease Control, who was researching the local slime population. This would not have been particularly exciting if not for his device, which stored the slimes and released them directly at me.~
@20257 = ~To repair his device for slime research, Pabeshts needs a shard from Lothar's lost golem. I do not want to get involved, but if I change my mind, I can find him near some poles by Suicide Falls.~
@20258 = ~To repair his device for slime research, Pabeshts needs a shard from Lothar's lost golem, which is supposedly located somewhere by the Knife on the River. I do not want to get involved, but if I change my mind, I can find Pabeshts near some poles by Suicide Falls.~
@20260 = ~Pabeshts received a golem shard to repair his device and, in return, he gave me vermin armor from the Lower Planes. It is not exactly my style, but I think I have an idea of how to use it.~
@20261 = ~Resolve a rotten intra-rat rivalry~
@20262 = ~Orville, the wererat barkeep at the Rat and Splat, wants Mantuok dead. Reportedly, Mantuok was last seen in the Bones of the Night beneath the Lower Ward.~
@20263 = ~I managed to convince Orville to abandon his vengeance and spare Mantuok's life. Given the barkeep's health, he would not have been able to enjoy it for long anyway.~
@20264 = ~Orville was pleased to learn of Mantuok's demise. It will be interesting to see what effect the death of someone involved in so many schemes will have on the wererat community.~
@20265 = ~Instead of looking for the entrance to the armory, I brought the stolen jade skull to Ulfbrand, the factotum of the Fated. It rightfully belonged to them, so it was only fair to return it.~
@20266 = ~Find out more about the split of Tyche into two goddesses~
@20267 = ~Ayryn Farlight, a Sensate scryer, told me the story of the ancient goddess Tyche, who split into two new goddesses: Tymora and Beshaba. Apparently, this happened when Tyche was corrupted and another goddess, Selûne, attempted to end her suffering. Recently, another god tried to reunite Tyche, which has renewed the Sensates' interest in this ancient event. However, the libraries in Sigil seem incomplete. I offered to search for additional information in the libraries of Mephistar if I have the chance. If I succeed, I will be handsomely rewarded. I will find Ayryn at the Civic Festhall when I return from Cania.~
@20268 = ~It seems that I will not visit Mephistar after all. I will not be able to find any tomes about Tyche's split into Tymora and Beshaba in the local library.~
